Excellent question. This is **critical** for Africa. Let me break down the real impact:

---

## ⚡ Performance Impact Analysis

### The Good News: Minimal Impact (If Done Right)

**Template rendering itself is FAST** because:
```typescript
// Template application = CSS class swap + JSON config
// No heavy computation

// Current (no template):
<div className="bg-white text-stone-900">

// With template:
<div className={template.colors.bg} style={{ '--primary': template.colors.primary }}>

// Difference: ~0.5ms render time
```

**What's actually loaded:**
- Template config: **<2KB JSON** (colors, fonts, layout flags)
- CSS variables: **Already in bundle** (no extra CSS file)
- Font family: **1 extra Google Font load** (~20-40KB if not cached)

**Total overhead: ~25-50KB** (vs. 2-5MB for photos)

---

### ⚠️ The Real Risks (Africa Context)

| Risk | Impact | Likelihood |
|------|--------|------------|
| **Multiple template previews** loading at once | High | 🔴 High (marketplace browsing) |
| **Heavy template animations** (parallax, transitions) | Critical | 🟡 Medium (designer creativity) |
| **External font loads** (3-4 font families) | High | 🔴 High (designer preference) |
| **Unoptimized template images** (hero backgrounds) | Critical | 🔴 High (common mistake) |
| **Client-side template switching** (re-renders) | Medium | 🟡 Medium (if not SSR) |

---

## 🛡️ Africa-First Template Performance Rules

### Mandatory Template Constraints (Enforced by Platform)

```typescript
// lib/types/templates.ts
export type TemplatePreset = {
  // ... existing fields

  // PERFORMANCE CONSTRAINTS (Africa-first)
  max_css_size_kb: 10,           // Template CSS additions <10KB
  max_font_families: 2,          // Max 2 custom fonts
  max_hero_image_kb: 100,        // Hero bg image <100KB
  allows_parallax: false,        // NO parallax scrolling
  allows_heavy_animations: false, // NO GSAP/complex animations
  requires_lazy_load: true,      // All images lazy-loaded
  critical_css_inlined: true,    // Above-fold CSS inlined
};
```

### Technical Implementation (Speed-Optimized)

#### 1. **Server-Side Template Application** (No Client JS)
```typescript
// app/pro/[slug]/page.tsx
export default async function ProfessionalProfile({ params }) {
  const professional = await getProfessional(params.slug);

  // Fetch template config (cached)
  const template = professional.template_id 
    ? await getTemplatePreset(professional.template_id)
    : DEFAULT_TEMPLATE;

  // Apply template server-side → HTML has final classes
  return (
    <div 
      className={template.layout.container}
      style={{
        '--color-primary': template.colors.primary,
        '--color-secondary': template.colors.secondary,
        '--font-heading': template.typography.heading_font,
      } as React.CSSProperties}
    >
      {/* Rendered HTML already has template classes */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

**Benefit**: Zero client-side JavaScript for template switching.

---

#### 2. **Critical CSS Inlining** (First Paint <1s on 3G)
```typescript
// lib/templates/critical-css.ts
export function getCriticalCSS(templateId: string) {
  // Return only CSS needed for above-fold content
  // ~5-8KB max
  return `
    .hero { min-height: 60vh; }
    .hero-title { font-size: 2rem; }
    /* Template-specific critical styles */
  `;
}

// In page.tsx
<style dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ 
  __html: getCriticalCSS(professional.template_id) 
}} />
```

---

#### 3. **Template Asset CDN with African Edge Locations**
```typescript
